  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6, then take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Add the <strong>sweetcorn cobettes</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> and top with a large knob of<strong> butter</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the corn until tightly sealed and add to a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the corn is tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1594129423917-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1594129423917-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1594129423917-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1594129423917-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1594129423917-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chicken breast portions </strong>to a bowl with the <strong>chipotle paste</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the<strong> cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika, </strong>1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and<strong> pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>marinated chicken</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up, then set aside</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1594129436390-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1594129436390-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1594129436390-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1594129436390-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1594129436390-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the chicken is marinating, chop the <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks, then peel and chop the <strong>garlic</strong> roughly</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and 50ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [100ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Blitz until you're left with a green liquid – this is your <strong>coriander paste</strong></p><p>Tip: No food processor? Chop everything up as finely as you can and mix it together!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1594129467293-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
