        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the chicken is cooking, trim, then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>finely</p><p>Once the corn is tender, spread the <strong>mayo</strong> around each <strong>cobette</strong> with the back of a spoon</p><p>Crumble the <strong>feta</strong> over the corn and add a pinch of the <strong>remaining cayenne pepper </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>elote corn</strong></p><p>Cut the<strong> lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>into wedges</p>",
